The 'todo' branch
=================

This is an orphan branch — it shares no history with 'main'. It holds the
maintainer's tooling and process artifacts for the gut project:

  Reintegrate        — per-topic merge primitive (echo TOPIC | ./Reintegrate)
  redo-next.sh       — declarative recipe to rebuild 'next' from 'main'
  redo-seen.sh       — declarative recipe to rebuild 'seen' from 'next'
  whats-cooking.txt  — current state of the integration tree
  README.cooking     — this file

Rationale: keep maintainer machinery off 'main' so the project tree stays
clean, but version-control the process so 'whats-cooking.txt' has real
history and the redo scripts are diffable across cycles. Modeled on the
Git project's own 'todo' branch (Junio C Hamano's setup since 2005).

Recommended use: mount this branch as a worktree at Meta/ inside your
'main' checkout, mirroring the convention in
~/repos/other/git/Documentation/howto/maintain-git.adoc:

    git worktree add Meta todo

Then 'Meta/Reintegrate', 'Meta/redo-seen.sh', etc. are live from a 'main'
shell. The 'Meta/' name is a worktree pin only — it is *not* a path on
the 'todo' branch itself.

The full maintainer playbook lives in .claude/skills/gut-maintainer/ on
'main'.
